#: ../../post_processing/wall_paper.rst:16
msgid "The Wall-Paper tool allows set an image from your collection as a background photo to your desktop. If you use a multi-screen computer, the image is assigned to the current monitor where digiKam is running."
msgstr ""

#: ../../post_processing/wall_paper.rst:18
msgid "Select one image that you want to push on your desktop and go to :menuselection:`Tools --> Set as wallpaper`, or use the icon **Set as walpaper** from the **Tools** tab on right sidebar. A dialog will appear to customize the **Wallpaper Layout** of background photo. The possible choices are listed below:"
msgstr ""

#: ../../post_processing/wall_paper.rst:20
msgid "**Adjusted**: The image is resized to the desktop size without to preserve aspect ratio (Linux and Windows)."
msgstr ""

#: ../../post_processing/wall_paper.rst:21
msgid "**Adjusted with Aspect ratio**: The image is resized to the desktop size preserving aspect ratio (Linux only)."
msgstr ""

#: ../../post_processing/wall_paper.rst:22
msgid "**Adjusted and cropped**: The image is resized to the desktop size and cropped to support desktop aspect ratio (Linux only)."
msgstr ""

#: ../../post_processing/wall_paper.rst:23
msgid "**Mosaic**: The image is displayed multi-time as a mosaic the fill desktop (Linux and Windows)."
msgstr ""

#: ../../post_processing/wall_paper.rst:24
msgid "**Centered**: The image is centered to the desktop without modification (Linux and Windows)."
msgstr ""

#: ../../post_processing/wall_paper.rst:28
msgid "This dialog do not exists under macOS. The layout is always set as **Centered**."
msgstr ""

